        Az8DaysP4:
          "This morning we will go for a walk around Sheki. One of the most ancient cities of Azerbaijan, Sheki is rightly called the architectural reserve of the country. We will visit one of the most important architectural monuments of Azerbaijan - the Palace of Sheki Khans (1762). After that, we will see the caravanserai in Sheki, which was famous for its trade. Also we will drive to Kish village located near Sheki. Kish, one of the oldest villages in the territory of the Azerbaijan is well-known with its unique architectural monument, a temple from the period of the Caucasian Albania. We will visit a local bakery. They will demonstrate us the “Khalva” master-class. Khalva is considered as dessert typical of Azerbaijan. Mainly it is made from flour, walnut, hazel, fat seed, butter and sugar. Overnight at the hotel in Sheki.(B/-/-)",
        Az8DaysD5: "Day 5: Sheki-Ganja (150 km)",
        Az8DaysP5:
          "Before leaving Sheki, we will go to Sheki’s Teze Bazaar, with its overflowing stalls of spice and fresh produce. After that, we will leave Sheki and travel to see one of the main historical and architectural cities – Ganja. Ganja is the second largest city in the country, a monument of the ancient culture. We will visit the “Bottle House”. In 1966-67, Ganja resident Ibrahim Jafarov used unusual material-glass bottles in the construction of his house. Totally 48,000 bottles of various shapes and sizes were used in the construction, and he also used colored stones brought from Sochi. Also we will see the 17th century Shah Abbas Mosque, Javad khan Mausoleum (XIX century), the Orthodox Church (1815). Overnight at the hotel in Ganja.(B/-/-)",
        Az8DaysD6: "Day 6: Ganja-Baku (370 km)",
        Az8DaysP6:
          "After breakfast we will see Nizami Mausoleum and Imamzade Mosque. We will leave Ganja for Baku. Arrival in Baku. Free evening in Baku. Overnight at the hotel in Baku. (B/-/-)",
        Az8DaysD7: "Day 7: Baku- Absheron-Baku (125 km)",
        Az8DaysP7:
          "After breakfast we will explore Zoroastrian Fire Temple Ateshgah in Surakhani settlement. Our next stop will be Yanar Dag Fire Mountain.  Yanar Dag is located 25 km to the north from Baku, in Mehemmedli village. The natural gas that seeps onto the surface gives this mountain its famous ‘burning’ look. Then, we will visit Heydar Aliyev Cultural Center (closed on Mondays). The building was designed by worldwide recognized Iraqi-British architect and Pritzker Prize winner Zaha Hadid in 2012. The building's design is characterized by its futuristic and fluid forms, featuring curves, waves, and a smooth white exterior. It has won numerous international architectural awards for its innovative and striking design. Overnight at the hotel in Baku. (B/-/-)",
        Az8DaysD8: "Day 8: Departure",
        Az8DaysP8: "Guided transfer to Baku Heydar Aliyev Airport. Departure.",

