        bakuTourP2:
          "Walking tour of the medieval walled city 'lcheri Sheher' and around: Complex of Shirvanshahs Palace, Maiden’s Tower (external view), Muhammad Mosque, Juma Mosque and the imposing mansions of the oil barons, built in the oil boom of 1870-1914. Then we will see Governors Garden, Philharmonic Building, Ismailia Building, Happiness Palace, Azerbaijani Literature Museum, Azerbaijani Carpet Museum, Little Venice, National Boulevard Baku, Highland Park, Alley of Martyrs, Flame Towers, Baku Funicular, Baku Puppet Theatre and Fountain Square. Later visit Heydar Aliyev Cultural Center. The building's design has won numerous international architectural awards for its innovative and striking design. Overnight at the hotel in Baku. ",
        bakuTourP3:
          "Discover all that Baku and its surroundings have to offer on this full-day tour. See the prehistoric petroglyphs at Gobustan National Park, learn about the mud volcanoes and their healing properties, visit the Zoroastrian fire temple of Ateshgah, and explore the fire mountain of Yanardag. Overnight at the hotel in Baku.",
